01:22:57.520 --> 01:22:58.440
Former partner.

01:22:59.640 --> 01:23:03.320
[Paula Yates] And do you think you'll be
very sad on the last concert?

01:23:03.400 --> 01:23:04.840
Or do you think it'll be jolly?

01:23:04.920 --> 01:23:06.480
-I think it'll be…
-[Andrew] Happy.

01:23:06.560 --> 01:23:08.600
[George] I think it'll be a bit of both.

01:23:08.680 --> 01:23:11.360
I think it'll be
probably the best concert we've ever done,

01:23:11.440 --> 01:23:13.720
and I think it'll be rather sad
that it's the last.

01:23:13.800 --> 01:23:17.320
-[Andrew] Disappointing if it isn't.
-Mm. Let's pray that it's a nice day.

01:23:17.400 --> 01:23:19.920
Let's all keep our fingers crossed
that the sun shines,

01:23:20.000 --> 01:23:23.680
God smiles upon us,
and Wham! ends as it began,

01:23:23.760 --> 01:23:25.080
with a smile on its face.

01:23:25.160 --> 01:23:26.320
[Andrew] Fantastic ending.

01:23:27.600 --> 01:23:29.880
-I love you.
-[Paula Yates] Tore at my heartstrings.

01:23:29.960 --> 01:23:31.000
[George sniffles]

01:23:31.080 --> 01:23:33.080
[crowd cheering]

01:23:37.120 --> 01:23:41.440
We want Wham!! We want Wham!!
We want Wham!! We want Wham!!

